INSERT INTO `blog4` VALUES (1,'2019-01-03','One pan lasagna','<p>\r\n1 pound ground beef<br>1 small onion (chopped)<br>Garlic Seasoning<br>Salt<br>Pepper<br>1 teaspoon italian seasoning<br>2 cups marinara sauce\r\n<br>1.5 cups pasta (dry mafalda)\r\n<br>1 Can chicken broth<br>1 cup mozzarella cheese (shredded)</p><p>&nbsp;Cook Ground beef in skillet and drain. <br>Leave out of skillet&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Add olive oil and butter. Cook onion 5 min.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Add marinara sauce, chicken broth.\r\nAdd garlic seasoning, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper. Stir.</p><p>&nbsp;Add ground beef and pasta.\r\nCook 15 min</p><p>&nbsp;Add mozzarella cheese.\r\n\r\nDone.</p>'),(2,'2019-02-26','Hamburger Rice Skillet','<p>1lb Ground Beef</p><p>Diced Onion</p><p>Diced Green Pepper</p><p>1 cup rice</p><p>1 can diced tomatoes</p><p>1 can tomato sauce</p><p>1 tsp Worcestershire sause</p><p>1/2 tsp dried basil</p><p>1 tsp Salt</p><p>1tsp garlic seasoning</p><p>Start rice in rice cooker. <br>Brown the ground beef and drain. Leave out of skillet.<br>Heat onion and green pepper in olive oil and butter in skillet. 5-7 minutes<br>Add diced tomatoes and tomato sauce.<br>Add Worcestershire, basil, salt, garlic seasoning and stir.</p><p>Add cooked ground beef.<br>Add cooked rice.</p>'),(3,'2019-02-27','One pan hamburger helper','\r\n<p>1lb ground beef</p><p>1 can beef broth</p><p>1.25 cups elbow macaroni</p><p>1 can tomato sauce</p><p>Diced onion</p><p>1tsp Garlic seasoning</p><p>Brown ground beef and drain. Leave out of skillet.<br>Heat onion in olive oil and butter.<br>Add beef broth and tomato sause.<br>Add Garlic seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.<br>Add elbow macaroni.<br>Heat for 15 minutes.</p><p>Serve with parmesan cheese.</p>\r\n'),(4,'2019-02-28','Salsbury Steak','\r\n<p>1 Can condensed French onion soup<br>1 l/2 lb ground beef<br>1/2 cup bread crumbs<br>1 egg<br>1/4 tsp salt<br>1/8 tsp pepper</p><p>Gravy</p><p>1 tbsp flour<br>1/4 cup ketchup<br>1/4 cup water<br>1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce<br>1/2 tsp mustard powder</p><p>In a large bowl mix 1/3 cup condensed French onion soup with groud beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.<br>Shape into 6 patties</p><p>In a large skillet brown both sides of patties. Pour off excess fat.</p><p>In a small bowl, blend flour and remaining soup until smooth. Mix in ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and mustard powder.&nbsp;</p><p>Pour over meat in skillet. Cover, and cook for 20 minutes.</p><p><a style=\"display:block;padding-bottom:10px;\" href=\"https://claytonfelt.smugmug.com/Around-the-House/Recipies/i-v73Z8MD\" alt=\"Smugmug link\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"640\" class=\"sel_image\" src=\"https://photos.smugmug.com/Around-the-House/Recipies/i-v73Z8MD/0/c971d610/640x400/salsbury_steak-640x400.jpg\"></a><br><br></p><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(5,'2020-01-09','Mongolian Beef','<h2 class=\"wprm-recipe-name wprm-block-text-bold\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.3em; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.8em; clear: none; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal;\">Easy Mongolian Beef Recipe</h2><div class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\"><h3 class=\"wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header wprm-block-text-bold\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.3em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; clear: none; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; margin-top: 1.2em !important;\">Ingredients</h3><div class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-group\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><h4 class=\"wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.3em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; clear: none; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; margin-top: 0.8em !important;\">Main Ingredients:</h4><ul class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredients\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: 0px; padding-inline-start: 0px;\"><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">14</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">ounces</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">of beef</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; opacity: 0.7;\">cut into 5mm thick</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">2</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07K6VD6DL/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ref=idea_lv_dp_ov_d&amp;ascsub&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=f42b7329b81a15d0513f225e52f54888&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of Chinese cooking wine</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1/3</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/SaltWorks-Mediterra-Mediterranean-Coarse-Grain/dp/B07JX294BQ/ref=as_li_ss_tl?keywords=sea+salt&amp;qid=1567654121&amp;s=grocery&amp;sr=1-23&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=f61d4d36b8b600634934b8ccd51672c1&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of salt</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1/2</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Jackies-Kitchen-Black-Pepper-Grinder/dp/B07LCYFR6J/ref=as_li_ss_tl?fpw=pantry&amp;keywords=black+pepper&amp;qid=1567654859&amp;s=pantry&amp;sr=8-9&amp;srs=7301146011&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=ce0509a1c99a798b772dfa2b5e727cb5&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of black pepper</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1/4</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">cup</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B074H67H5C/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B074H67H5C&amp;linkId=16e02b5c0d4150c4fe648cd94527b8a0\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of cornstarch</a></span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; opacity: 0.7;\">just enough to coat the beef</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">egg white from 1.5 large egg</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">of minced ginger</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1.5</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">of minced garlic</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">a bunch of spring onion</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; opacity: 0.7;\">use the white part to stir fry and reserve the green part to add at the end</span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07PC8CC3B/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B07PC8CC3B&amp;linkId=8e04100c0ec98372ed10929abf1a3d6d\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">enough oil to fry the beef</a></span></li></ul></div><div class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-group\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><h4 class=\"wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.3em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; clear: none; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; margin-top: 0.8em !important;\">For the sauce:</h4><ul class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredients\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: 0px; padding-inline-start: 0px;\"><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">2</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B074H67H5C/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B074H67H5C&amp;linkId=16e02b5c0d4150c4fe648cd94527b8a0\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of cornstarch</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01MSZCY4U/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ref=idea_lv_dp_ov_d&amp;ascsub&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=424e239f254d0d0e630d7749a838992e&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of oyster sauce</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">3</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07PGWZCT6/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ref=idea_lv_dp_ov_d&amp;ascsub&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=b8631050e19e62d90a7971e6db5d7ffc&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of soy sauce</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">3</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tbsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B008XJWZM6/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B008XJWZM6&amp;linkId=8365c7923c37e24537e3e40fa3badb45\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of brown sugar</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">2/3</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">cup</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B007PZELRG/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B007PZELRG&amp;linkId=075844bdccc73b1a0607d3e4a8be5b55\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of water</a></span></li><li class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">1</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">tsp</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wprm-recipe-ingredient-name\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0001EJ4C0/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ref=idea_lv_dp_ov_d&amp;ascsub&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=printable-recipe-ingredient-link-20&amp;linkId=5607703160ce05b372638cba02a9336f&amp;language=en_US\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(52, 152, 219);\">of dark soy sauce</a></span></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\"><h3 class=\"wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header wprm-block-text-bold\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.3em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; clear: none; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; margin-top: 1.2em !important;\">Instructions</h3><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-group\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><ul class=\"wprm-recipe-instructions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: 0px; padding-inline-start: 0px;\"><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-0\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">My first tip for you is to slice the beef into 5 mm thick. Personally, I think this is the perfect thickness. I donâ€™t recommend slicing it thinner than this because it will dry out quickly during the frying.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-1\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Normally I will season it with some Chinese cooking wine. But I am in Cuenca Ecuador now. I couldnâ€™t find Chinese cooking wine in this whole city so I found out that same amount of beer works just fine. I thought this will be a good substitution for Chinese cooking wine. Do not use the dark beer. It will turn out a bit of bitter at the end. After that, I will add some salt and black pepper. If you get a cheap cut which might be tough, you can add 1/4 tsp of baking soda. It will help tenderize the beef. But if you get a nice cut, it is not necessary.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-2\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Let the beef sit for 30 minutes. We will coat the beef with some cornstarch. Give it a little mix to make sure the cornstarch is distributed so it wonâ€™t clump up later. Then we will add 1 and a half of egg white. Mix it again. After you make sure that every piece is coated nicely, you still want to keep massaging it for another 5 minutes to give it enough time to tenderize the meat. So this is my second tips. Cornstarch and egg white is a very common technique in Chinese cuisine. It gives a lot of moisture to the beef and creates a starchy layer to lock the juiciness inside the meat. So the beef will turn out super tender and juicy. Try it and you will be surprised.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-3\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Heat up 2 cups of frying oil to 370 degrees Fahrenheit. The most important thing is to get the oil to the high temperature so the beef will have a nice outside layer.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-4\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">I usually put the beef as close as possible to the oil and then drop it in. In this way, the oil wonâ€™t splash everywhere. Add your beef piece by piece otherwise, they will clump up together. Make sure you fry them in batches because it overflows easily.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-5\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">The oil is very hot so it will just take 1 or 2 minutes. Donâ€™t fry it too long because you donâ€™t want to overcook your beef. What we are looking for is the slightly golden color on the edge of the beef. I use a sieve to get rid of the excess oil.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-6\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Before we start the stir-frying process, letâ€™s quickly make the sauce(2 tsp of cornstarch, 1 tbsp of oyster sauce, 3 tbsp of soy sauce, 3 tbsp of brown sugar, 2/3 cup of water, 1 tsp of dark soy sauce). Set the sauce aside, we will use it soon.</div></li><li id=\"wprm-recipe-1224-step-0-7\" class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin: 0px 0px 0px 32px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: outside; position: relative; list-style-type: decimal; line-height: 1.5em !important;\"><div class=\"wprm-recipe-instruction-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1em; margin-bottom: 5px;\">Heat up the pan. Add about 1.5 tbsp of cooking oil, 1 tbsp of minced ginger, 1.5 tbsp of minced garlic, and some white part of the spring onion. I like to use the white part for stir-frying because they donâ€™t get soggy and I also reserved the green part to add at the end. Stir this until fragrant. Pour in the sauce. Stir it until it thickens up. Add the beef back into the pan. Mix everything together. Once you see the beef is coated with that shiny, thick, flavorful sauce, you can add some spring onion. Give it a final stir then take it out and serve it with white rice.</div></li></ul></div></div>\r\n\r\n'),(6,'2020-01-09','Sweet and sour chicken','\r\n\r\