gin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-right: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px; border-image: initial; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; box-shadow: none !important;\"><h4 data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 1.125em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(36, 41, 46); font-size: 1.15rem; box-shadow: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 239); padding-bottom: 0.3em; clear: both;\"><span class=\"text-node\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">Preparation</span></h4><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"526.15625\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">1. Cut the meat into large dices roughly 2cm3 and place in a large prep bowl.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"481.34375\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">2. Marinade in the sesame oil, sugar, light soy sauce and salt &amp; pepper.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"354.046875\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">3. Add the egg to the marinated meat and mix well.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"34\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"728.0625\" data-pf_rect_height=\"31\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">4. Add the seasoned corn flour and massage into the meat until each piece of meat separates. Continue to add flour until a dry â€˜dusty white\' consistency is reached.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"650.9375\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">5. If using any of the optional vegetables, cut into large dices and place in separate prep bowls.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"657.296875\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">6. Mix the tomato ketchup, vinegar and sugar and a dash of dark soy sauce in a small prep bowl.</p1></p><h4 data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 1.125em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(36, 41, 46); font-size: 1.15rem; box-shadow: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 239); padding-bottom: 0.3em; clear: both;\"><span class=\"text-node\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">Cooking</span></h4><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><em data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"622.453125\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">Please note: the key to a good sweet and sour is to ensure the meat is as crispy as possible.</em></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"558.859375\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">7. Deep fry the marinated meat at 170Â°C until golden brown (roughly 6-7 minutes)</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"420.125\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">8. Remove and strain of any excess oil on some kitchen towel.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"456.75\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">9. On a separate hob heat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a wok - high heat.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"653.3125\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">10. Add any optional vegetables , turn the heat down to medium heat and stir-fry for 2 minutes.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"265.578125\" data-pf_rect_height=\"14\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">11. Immediately add the sauce mixture.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"34\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><p1 data-pf_style_display=\"inline\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"733.09375\" data-pf_rect_height=\"31\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">12. Once the sauce starts to boil, throw the meat into the wok and give it one big stir before taking the wok off the heat.</p1></p><p data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" class=\"added-to-list1\" orig-style=\"null\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; box-shadow: none !important;\"><span class=\"text-node\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; box-shadow: none !important;\">N.B. the key to a good sweet and sour is to have just enough sauce to wrap around the crispy pieces of meat.</span></p><h4 data-pf_style_display=\"block\" data-pf_style_visibility=\"visible\" data-pf_rect_width=\"748\" data-pf_rect_height=\"17\" orig-style=\"null\" class=\"pf-delete\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 1.125em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(36, 41, 46); font-size: 1.15rem; cursor: pointer; position: relative; box-shadow: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 239); padding-bottom: 0.3em; clear: both;\"><span class=\"text-node\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; cursor: pointer; position: relative; color: rgba(179, 151,